      "description": "This 2007 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) is a mechanically sound example of Zuffenhausen engineering, perfect for the purist. Powered by a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, the M97 engine delivers linear power with the unmistakable boxer cadence. The 6-speed manual transaxle offers short, precise throws, sending power to the rear wheels with tactile engagement. This specimen is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), providing variable damping rates to maintain chassis composure during high-lateral-G maneuvers. The braking system features four-piston monobloc aluminum calipers paired with cross-drilled, ventilated rotors for superior thermal management and firm pedal modulation. Recent preventative maintenance includes an IMS bearing inspection and a fresh rear main seal. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with spirited road use, the hydraulic steering remains communicative and the drivetrain is exceptionally tight.",
